title: Amphiplica plutonica
text:
Amphiplica plutonica is a <a href="species">species</a> of <a href="sea%20snail">sea snail</a>, a marine <a href="gastropod">gastropod</a> <a href="mollusk">mollusk</a> in the <a href="family%20%28biology%29">family</a> <a href="Caymanabyssiidae">Caymanabyssiidae</a>.
Distribution.
This marine species was found in the <a href="Cayman%20Trench">Cayman Trench</a>.
Description.
The maximum recorded <a href="gastropod%20shell">shell</a> length is 10.8 mm.
Habitat.
Minimum recorded depth is 6600 m. Maximum recorded depth is 7225 m.
